data.title: Santa Maria Coghinas: the XVIII edition of the Beer Festival begins
data.meta_description: Santa Maria Coghinas: the XVIII edition of the Beer Festival begins
data.text:
Everything is ready for one of the most popular events of the summer in Santa Maria Coghinas. The Cuzinesa beer festival, now in its eighth edition, will liven up the weekend of the small but lively town of Anglona. A weekend dedicated to fun with an important warning: drink consciously. An event, organized by a group of young people assisted by the Proloco, which has always attracted up to three thousand people at the weekend, which this year will be packed with tourists and curious people from all over the island.

On 19 and 20 July, opening at 7pm, in the sports field opposite the padel court, the appointment is with the celebration not only of beer but of the community, families and children. In fact, both Saturday and Sunday there will be entertainment with inflatable games, soap bubbles, small basketball tournaments and face painting. There will also be room for adults to have fun with the IV padel tournament which will start on Friday 19th with the qualifiers and semi-finals and final on Saturday 20th.

Both evenings will be accompanied by good music: we start on Friday 19th with an aperitif before sunset with the music of DJ Nicol Peru with commercial user sounds; the Funny groove band will follow, with a repertoire that traces the great international hits of the 80s to end with disco dance and special light effects.

On Saturday 20th the evening will begin at 9pm with disco music history with What If, who will present the history of disco music, special guest Kim Lukas. Dj Omar will conclude the evening with house music, tek house with commercial sounds, and his repertoire will be all to dance to. In the sports field area there will be a cocktail corner and it will be possible to taste take-away food.

 Riproduzione riservata
